We would like to thank you again for your continued support. We promise to do the best we can to ensure the safety of our community üåà

We have learned a lot from this and have put more measures into place such as providing more NFT safety information to our community members in our discord, educating and informing our team on what current hacks/scams are on-trend, and additional security audits of our server.
We are also investigating the members that were affected by this unfortunate event.

One of our MODS had a cold admin account and was able to regain control of the server within 20 mins. 

We take server security and the safety of our community seriously. We had a security audit of our server last March and are doing another one as we approach our launch.

As you may know, our server got hacked on May 13 around 3:50am AEST. 

The attack happened while the dev team was asleep. We wanted to take this chance to thank our MODS and community who were awake at that time and informed the community that the server had been hacked.
